#  Author:       Iwan Kwrakow
#
#  Contributors: Ernesto Mainegra-Hing
#
###############################################################################
#
#  This file is processed by the make_distribution utility
#  to produce unix tar-files (uncompressed, compressed and gziped)
#  as well as the distribution format used by the graphical installer.
#
#  Syntax:
#  - Lines starting with # are comments and are therefore ignored
#  - Blank lines are ignored as well
#  - Lines in the form
#      tarfile: some_tar_file_name
#    start a new distribution file named (version)some_tar_file_name.tar
#      where version is defined in the first line.
#  - The list must end with a line beginning with
#    end list
#  - All other lines are considered to describe files to be included in
#    the currently active archive. All files must include their path relative
#    to the EGSnrc root directory
#      * A single file name on a line makes the file to be included in the
#        currently active archive
#      * A single directory on a line makes all files in that directory
#        (including under-directories) to get included in the
#        currently active archive
#      * Two file or directory names on a line makes the file/directory
#        given by the first name to be included in the archive under the
#        name given by the second name
#      * Lines beginning with
#          win:
#          unix:
#        mean that the subsequent file/directory will only get included,
#        if we are preparing a distribution for Windows or Unix.
#        (this is determined via a command line argument of the
#        make_distribution utility). Lines starting with win: or unix:
#        behave otherwise as described above, i.e. there may be one or
#        two file/directory names on the line.
#
###############################################################################


#*****************************************************************************
#
# The main EGSnrc file
#
#*****************************************************************************

